1
00:00:02,458 --> 00:00:03,958
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:06,542 --> 00:00:07,958
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:10,167 --> 00:00:12,125
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:16,250
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:20,167
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:29,833
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 8)

7
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:33,833
Oh!

8
00:00:33,958 --> 00:00:34,958
What?

9
00:00:35,083 --> 00:00:36,833
Wait, is my dad really here?

10
00:00:36,958 --> 00:00:39,417
Yes, it's His Majesty the Emperor.

11
00:00:39,542 --> 00:00:40,542
Contact him! Hurry!

12
00:00:40,625 --> 00:00:42,208
But Prince, I can't get this to connect.

13
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:45,573
I think it's probably because of the device
interference with the communications on Earth.

14
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:47,958
Hachi! Are you messing with me?

15
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:49,208
Prince, it's true!

16
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:50,542
You know Hachi can't lie.

17
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:54,167
His Majesty clearly said that
he entered our solar system.

18
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:56,125
Did he say anything else?

19
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:57,370
It's just my opinion, but...

20
00:00:57,458 --> 00:00:59,333
I think His Majesty has brought a fleet.

21
00:00:59,458 --> 00:01:00,917
A fleet?

22
00:01:01,042 --> 00:01:03,458
Is he here to conquer Earth?

23
00:01:03,583 --> 00:01:05,708
His Majesty, invading Earth?

24
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:07,250
Stop talking nonsense.

25
00:01:07,375 --> 00:01:10,000
You guys can play your royal games.

26
00:01:10,417 --> 00:01:12,292
I'm going to find my brother.

27
00:01:12,417 --> 00:01:13,708
I'm coming too.

28
00:01:14,792 --> 00:01:15,792
Wait!

29
00:01:15,917 --> 00:01:16,750
I wanna go too.

30
00:01:16,875 --> 00:01:18,434
Our Princess should probably be there too.

31
00:01:18,458 --> 00:01:19,167
Boss!

32
00:01:19,292 --> 00:01:22,250
Okay, where are we going to find Woo-hyuk?

33
00:01:22,375 --> 00:01:23,833
We have to check everywhere.

34
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:27,167
Okay, wait. I know someone
who might know where he is.

35
00:01:27,292 --> 00:01:28,875
Would you like to go see him?

36
00:01:39,042 --> 00:01:40,708
(Return)

37
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:30,125
Ugh... damn it...

38
00:02:33,792 --> 00:02:35,083
Soon-nam.

39
00:02:35,208 --> 00:02:37,083
You're surprisingly sharp.

40
00:02:37,917 --> 00:02:39,458
Is it this way?

41
00:02:40,083 --> 00:02:40,875
Officer Shin.

42
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,583
I mean, he's not much of a talker,

43
00:02:42,708 --> 00:02:44,458
but he's incredibly smart.

44
00:02:54,042 --> 00:02:56,875
Let's go together! Huh?

45
00:02:59,708 --> 00:03:01,417
What's wrong?

46
00:03:01,542 --> 00:03:02,833
I didn't even call for you.

47
00:03:02,958 --> 00:03:06,708
We're here to say that the Emperor has already
entered the solar system with his fleet.

48
00:03:07,292 --> 00:03:08,125
W-what?

49
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:11,958
Looks like we need to change the plan.

50
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:13,208
C-change the plan?

51
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:16,167
We don't have time to slowly
harvest Earth's energy anymore.

52
00:03:16,292 --> 00:03:18,125
We don't have time for that.

53
00:03:18,792 --> 00:03:20,472
We need to extract all the energy at once,

54
00:03:20,542 --> 00:03:21,875
and leave Earth immediately.

55
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,875
Are you... are you insane?!

56
00:03:24,292 --> 00:03:26,542
That will kill every living thing on Earth!

57
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:27,667
What about our money?

58
00:03:27,792 --> 00:03:29,833
What about our investors?

59
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:45,250
Forget it, let's just go.

60
00:03:56,792 --> 00:03:57,875
Good grief.

61
00:04:01,042 --> 00:04:02,083
Wait a second.

62
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,833
Why are we heading up?

63
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:06,000
Can't you tell? We're catching the culprit.

64
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:07,125
We're on our way up now.

65
00:04:07,208 --> 00:04:08,958
He's got a gun!

66
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,208
I have a gun too, don't I?

67
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:14,000
Isn't that... the memory-erasing gun?

68
00:04:14,125 --> 00:04:15,000
That's right.

69
00:04:15,125 --> 00:04:16,958
Isn't that broken?

70
00:04:20,625 --> 00:04:21,875
Huh?

71
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,542
It works perfectly fine.

72
00:04:29,167 --> 00:04:30,333
Hey, this guy...

73
00:04:30,458 --> 00:04:31,476
Is he really going to be okay?

74
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:32,917
He'll wake up in a few hours.

75
00:04:33,042 --> 00:04:34,417
I calculated the shot perfectly.

76
00:04:34,542 --> 00:04:35,625
His memory will be fine.

77
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:37,250
Alright, let's go catch the culprit.

78
00:04:37,375 --> 00:04:39,208
Are we just going to leave him here?

79
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,601
It's safer for him to sleep here.

80
00:04:40,625 --> 00:04:43,125
- No way...
- He wouldn't be any help anyway.

81
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:48,917
You're cold-blooded.

82
00:04:49,042 --> 00:04:52,000
Poor alien, you've drained him dry.

83
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,917
Vampire boss.

84
00:04:58,875 --> 00:04:59,917
Do you know what this is?

85
00:05:00,042 --> 00:05:02,417
A self-destruct device.

86
00:05:02,542 --> 00:05:05,250
Boom, boom, boom.

87
00:05:05,875 --> 00:05:07,375
If I press this, you're all finished.

88
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,167
The harvester will blow up too.

89
00:05:15,292 --> 00:05:16,292
Then press it.

90
00:05:16,375 --> 00:05:17,583
Oh...

91
00:05:23,458 --> 00:05:24,708
Coward.

92
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,458
You think I won't press it?

93
00:05:27,583 --> 00:05:29,333
You're really underestimating me.

94
00:05:29,458 --> 00:05:30,917
Press it!

95
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:50,208
Oh, Chairman, you're so cute, aren't you?

96
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:52,375
Chairman.

97
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:54,708
You've worked hard all this time.

98
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:56,208
Rest in peace.

99
00:05:57,458 --> 00:06:00,833
Wait... before you go, I
have something to say.

100
00:06:00,958 --> 00:06:03,417
Chairman, you remember the plan, right?

101
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:08,875
It started when I gave you the
blueprints for the energy harvester.

102
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,042
Remember?

103
00:06:11,625 --> 00:06:16,583
Actually... I stole them from the palace.

104
00:06:17,542 --> 00:06:19,167
The truth is...

105
00:06:19,958 --> 00:06:24,250
I used to be a palace guard.

106
00:06:25,125 --> 00:06:26,375
This is getting interesting.

107
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:29,667
Why not just give it to him?
What's with the proposal?

108
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,208
Chairman, I really admire you.

109
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:37,000
W-well then...

110
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:40,250
No... no! Don't shoot!

111
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:41,833
- Don't shoot...
- No!

112
00:06:41,958 --> 00:06:43,625
Don't shoot!

113
00:06:48,250 --> 00:06:50,250
That should keep us from being suspected.

114
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:13,125
Are we really going the right way?

115
00:07:14,292 --> 00:07:15,750
Didn't Hachi say it was this way?

116
00:07:15,862 --> 00:07:19,070
Why trust him? Hachi
gets lost all the time.

117
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:22,917
I can sense various signals of
interference coming from that direction.

118
00:07:23,042 --> 00:07:24,458
Interfering with communications...

119
00:07:24,583 --> 00:07:25,750
And landing on Earth?

120
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:28,458
Yes, if my senses are correct.

121
00:07:28,958 --> 00:07:30,000
A river!

122
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:32,542
That's a river!

123
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:34,625
Such precious water...

124
00:07:35,535 --> 00:07:38,368
There's so much of it... it's amazing.

125
00:07:40,417 --> 00:07:43,667
Precious water? Are you from a desert?

126
00:07:43,792 --> 00:07:45,292
A desert?

127
00:07:48,792 --> 00:07:50,750
Any place without Wooju...

128
00:07:51,417 --> 00:07:52,833
is a desert to me.

129
00:07:58,958 --> 00:08:00,583
What are you talking about?

130
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,042
Wooju.

131
00:08:10,708 --> 00:08:13,708
To me...

132
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:17,750
you are as precious as water.

133
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:27,583
Wow! Look at that.

134
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:29,708
People are riding bicycles!

135
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:31,292
I want to ride a bicycle.

136
00:08:31,417 --> 00:08:32,417
Me too.

137
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:37,000
What? You've never ridden a bike before?

138
00:08:37,125 --> 00:08:38,625
Let's ride that.

139
00:08:40,542 --> 00:08:43,042
How poor are you guys?
You've never seen a bike?

140
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:04,042
Um... is this a suicide?

141
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:06,750
Doesn't look like it. Why
would they commit suicide?

142
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:10,000
Hey, is alien blood blue?

143
00:09:10,118 --> 00:09:12,177
It can be red, orange, yellow,
green, blue, indigo, or violet.

144
00:09:12,208 --> 00:09:13,288
Every species is different.

145
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:14,083
If it were suicide,

146
00:09:14,208 --> 00:09:16,018
they wouldn't hold a
gun to their own forehead.

147
00:09:16,042 --> 00:09:17,167
Exactly.

148
00:09:17,292 --> 00:09:18,852
This was staged to look like a suicide.

149
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:21,917
Wait... who could it be?

150
00:09:25,542 --> 00:09:26,583
I'm taking this.

151
00:09:26,708 --> 00:09:27,875
Hey, you can't.

152
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,042
This is evidence.

153
00:09:29,167 --> 00:09:29,833
I can't?

154
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:32,542
No, it has to be kept
at the police station.

155
00:09:32,667 --> 00:09:34,542
No matter how much you want it,

156
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:36,667
you shouldn't touch a
dead person's belongings.

157
00:09:36,792 --> 00:09:39,417
I know whose ring this is.

158
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,083
Whose?

159
00:09:41,208 --> 00:09:43,083
It's Prince Raon's mother's.

160
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,083
Really?

161
00:09:45,208 --> 00:09:47,417
Yes, I'll make sure to deliver it for you.

162
00:09:47,542 --> 00:09:51,542
Even so, we have to wait until
the police investigation is over.

163
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,125
Senior.

164
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:57,417
This looks like a suicide
note in the envelope, but...

165
00:09:57,542 --> 00:10:00,583
What is this? Alien language?

166
00:10:00,917 --> 00:10:03,542
Hmm... this is...

167
00:10:03,667 --> 00:10:04,708
What does it say?

168
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,792
He says he poisoned the Queen.

169
00:10:06,917 --> 00:10:08,958
And it says after coming to Earth,

170
00:10:09,083 --> 00:10:10,976
he killed the baker couple
who were close to the King.

171
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:14,500
Wait, who is the Queen?
And who are the bakers...

172
00:10:14,625 --> 00:10:15,625
No...

173
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:17,583
Ah! You scared me! A zombie!

174
00:10:17,708 --> 00:10:18,292
What is this?
Zombie! Zombie!

175
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:21,917
What? Are you awake?

176
00:10:23,917 --> 00:10:26,458
Hey, are you awake?

177
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,833
My head... ah...

178
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:33,333
Are you okay?

179
00:10:34,417 --> 00:10:37,875
Wait... how is he still alive?
He was shot in the forehead.

180
00:10:41,542 --> 00:10:44,417
No! I pressed this button.

181
00:10:44,542 --> 00:10:46,000
What is this button?

182
00:10:46,125 --> 00:10:47,708
It's a bit complicated.

183
00:10:47,832 --> 00:10:50,308
It's a device that prevents death
even if you're shot by an Earth gun.

184
00:10:50,333 --> 00:10:52,309
I pretended it was a self-destruct
button when I pressed it.

185
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:55,208
Do you know who the culprit is?

186
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:58,958
It's that guy... Secretary
Lee is the culprit!

187
00:10:59,083 --> 00:11:01,417
Isn't he working with them? Why?

188
00:11:01,542 --> 00:11:04,625
They're going to destroy
Earth, and I don't want that!

189
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:06,042
Who would believe that?

190
00:11:06,167 --> 00:11:08,250
Exactly, you even
locked us in the basement!

191
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:10,935
I'll explain everything later.
Please, trust me one more time...

192
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,250
Mr. Wooju might know something!

193
00:11:14,292 --> 00:11:15,125
Wooju is in danger.
Hurry, we have to find Wooju.

194
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:17,750
Hey... let's go...

195
00:11:18,667 --> 00:11:21,000
No! Let's go together, together...

196
00:11:21,125 --> 00:11:24,708
My head hurts... my head
hurts, let's go together!

197
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:30,083
Is this the place?

198
00:11:30,208 --> 00:11:31,458
Yeah.

199
00:11:32,542 --> 00:11:35,042
Is hyung here?

200
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,375
Go, go, go!

201
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:28,333
Impressive.

202
00:12:29,125 --> 00:12:31,375
I didn't think you'd
actually find this place.

203
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,667
That's enough.

204
00:12:34,208 --> 00:12:34,875
Stop it.

205
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,625
Why?

206
00:12:37,708 --> 00:12:39,542
If it's money you want,
I can give it to you.

207
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:44,208
You sound exactly like the Queen.

208
00:12:44,333 --> 00:12:46,143
Your mother said the
exact same thing back then.

209
00:12:46,167 --> 00:12:48,792
She said she'd pay whatever it took.

210
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:50,667
My mother?

211
00:12:50,792 --> 00:12:54,875
Prince, that guy... wasn't he
the Queen's bodyguard?

212
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,708
I think he was.

213
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:07,750
It was you...

214
00:13:09,292 --> 00:13:10,917
You killed my mother?

215
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:18,250
That's right. No point in hiding it now.

216
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:19,708
That's right.

217
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:24,042
I poisoned the bread
made by the royal baker.

218
00:13:25,042 --> 00:13:26,792
You poisoned my mother...!

219
00:13:26,917 --> 00:13:28,292
Damn it...

220
00:13:30,743 --> 00:13:31,886
You didn't just kill my mother...

221
00:13:31,917 --> 00:13:35,792
You framed Wooju's father for it too...

222
00:13:37,625 --> 00:13:40,167
Then you came to Earth
and killed Wooju's parents...!

223
00:13:42,417 --> 00:13:45,333
Raon... I have no idea
what you're talking about.

224
00:13:47,042 --> 00:13:48,792
What are you guys saying...

225
00:13:49,417 --> 00:13:51,042
What is going on?!

226
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:55,667
This jerk...

227
00:13:59,042 --> 00:14:04,042
He's the one who killed
my mother and your parents!

228
00:14:04,167 --> 00:14:05,167
Is all of this true?

229
00:14:06,417 --> 00:14:08,083
That's all in the past!

230
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:10,958
The past? You call this the past?

231
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,333
Damn it.

232
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:23,583
Wooju!

233
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:26,125
Wooju!

234
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:34,625
No...

235
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,667
Ah!

236
00:14:38,958 --> 00:14:40,417
Damn it...

237
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:44,667
Wooju, hang in there...

238
00:14:49,583 --> 00:14:50,917
Wooju!

239
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:56,042
Just hold on!

240
00:14:56,167 --> 00:14:57,500
Wooju!

241
00:15:12,042 --> 00:15:13,458
Get out of my way!

242
00:15:19,208 --> 00:15:20,608
Where are you in such a rush to go?

243
00:15:20,667 --> 00:15:22,625
Get lost, you fucker!

244
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:29,208
Come out here! You bastard!

245
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:31,417
You are under arrest for murder.

246
00:15:31,542 --> 00:15:33,292
You have the right to remain silent.

247
00:15:33,417 --> 00:15:34,875
Let go of me! Get your hands off me!

248
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:35,875
Let go! Damn it...

249
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,000
Stay still, you punk...

250
00:15:37,042 --> 00:15:39,125
I'm going to shut down
the energy harvester.

251
00:15:43,292 --> 00:15:45,292
(Wooju Bakery)

252
00:15:47,042 --> 00:15:48,667
It's all over now.

253
00:15:49,625 --> 00:15:52,167
What about this alien?

254
00:15:52,292 --> 00:15:54,958
- We can't take him to the station.
- Just stay still, damn it.

255
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:42,083
What happened to that guy with the knife?

256
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:46,792
What are you talking about?
You must've been dreaming.

257
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:49,625
I swear I got stabbed
for you and collapsed...

258
00:16:54,542 --> 00:17:00,333
That's strange... Was it just a dream?

259
00:17:01,375 --> 00:17:07,500
Why would you take a
knife for me in a dream?

260
00:17:07,625 --> 00:17:12,042
Because I don't want to
lose... a person important to me.

261
00:17:14,417 --> 00:17:16,125
Am I important to you?

262
00:17:17,917 --> 00:17:21,750
Of course. But I think I
find you more important...

263
00:17:21,875 --> 00:17:23,625
Than you value me.

264
00:17:26,292 --> 00:17:27,958
What's that supposed to mean?

265
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:34,042
Never mind... Why am I suddenly so sleepy?

266
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,875
Get some rest.

267
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:07,167
Why did you use the memory eraser on Wooju?

268
00:18:07,292 --> 00:18:09,458
He never believed in aliens to begin with.

269
00:18:09,583 --> 00:18:12,625
If he knew he had alien blood in him...

270
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:14,458
He'd be completely overwhelmed.

271
00:18:14,583 --> 00:18:16,750
I didn't wipe his memory completely.

272
00:18:16,875 --> 00:18:22,042
I just made it feel like a hazy dream.

273
00:18:23,958 --> 00:18:28,875
Is it really okay to keep it from him?

274
00:18:29,958 --> 00:18:34,042
Wooju used to be so gloomy.

275
00:18:34,167 --> 00:18:36,000
He's only recently started to open up.

276
00:18:36,125 --> 00:18:38,750
I don't want him to go back
to having a hard time, Raon.

277
00:18:43,958 --> 00:18:46,292
I want to be by Wooju's side
even through the tough times.

278
00:18:48,875 --> 00:18:53,875
Isn't it more important to make
the person you love happy?

279
00:18:57,625 --> 00:19:03,583
Even if Wooju finds out everything...

280
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:06,583
I'm confident I can make him happy.

281
00:19:06,708 --> 00:19:07,958
Raon.

282
00:19:08,708 --> 00:19:10,125
Here.

283
00:19:13,542 --> 00:19:14,375
What is this?

284
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,958
It's your mother's keepsake.

285
00:19:16,083 --> 00:19:19,083
It's still being held as police evidence.

286
00:19:19,208 --> 00:19:20,875
I'll be going now.

287
00:19:45,625 --> 00:19:50,375
I truly hope you find happiness, Wooju.

288
00:20:18,042 --> 00:20:19,458
The Emperor!?

289
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:24,792
Hachi, I'll be landing near you soon.

290
00:20:24,917 --> 00:20:26,208
Prepare for my arrival.

291
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:29,167
Yes, I will... Wait, what?

292
00:20:29,292 --> 00:20:31,208
But how did you know the coordinates?

293
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:35,667
Hmph... Princess Q told me everything.

294
00:20:35,792 --> 00:20:37,125
Be ready.

295
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:41,208
We're in trouble... we're in big trouble!

296
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:44,708
Hachi! Is he coming here?

297
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:46,583
Boss! Prince!

298
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,792
- Wait... Hachi, wait!
- Prince!

299
00:20:50,042 --> 00:20:53,125
Boss! Prince! His Majesty's about to land!

300
00:20:54,208 --> 00:20:55,208
What?!

301
00:20:55,292 --> 00:20:56,125
Who's coming?

302
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:58,958
Look at that window! Right there!

303
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:02,250
Right there!

304
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:03,833
Oh my god.

305
00:21:03,958 --> 00:21:06,292
Look! Over there! Let's go.

306
00:21:08,375 --> 00:21:09,458
Where are we going now?

307
00:21:09,583 --> 00:21:11,875
To the place where they
make bread at Wooju Bakery.

308
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,458
Can this thing even make it there?

309
00:21:14,542 --> 00:21:18,333
And isn't this thing... still broken?

310
00:21:18,458 --> 00:21:19,708
It's fixed.

311
00:21:21,292 --> 00:21:22,372
This car is acting weird...

312
00:21:22,458 --> 00:21:24,208
I told you, it's a spaceship.

313
00:21:55,542 --> 00:21:57,875
Mr. Kim was able to leave the Earth.

314
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:00,792
He finally returned to his family.

315
00:22:00,917 --> 00:22:04,000
Of course, some chose to stay.

316
00:22:04,875 --> 00:22:06,458
You ask why?

317
00:22:07,208 --> 00:22:08,292
I love this one!

318
00:22:08,417 --> 00:22:11,125
Some stay because they love Earth's food.

319
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:12,667
How much for this?

320
00:22:13,417 --> 00:22:16,333
Others stay because
they love Earth's music.

321
00:22:19,333 --> 00:22:21,875
Why did you bring these guys here?

322
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,760
We couldn't take them
to the police station.

323
00:22:23,875 --> 00:22:25,125
No one would believe us anyway.

324
00:22:25,250 --> 00:22:27,184
Didn't you say someone from Wooju's side
would come to pick them up soon?

325
00:22:27,208 --> 00:22:29,125
Let's just keep them here for now.

326
00:22:29,250 --> 00:22:33,250
By the way, are you two dating?

327
00:22:34,917 --> 00:22:36,833
Who said we're dating?

328
00:22:38,542 --> 00:22:40,458
And some people...

329
00:22:41,792 --> 00:22:43,417
stay for love.
